sep.gaia.resources.tiles2d

Class TileResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • sep.gaia.resources.DataResource
      • sep.gaia.resources.tiles2d.TileResource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TileResource
extends DataResource
    Concrete class TileResource. TileResource represents a image tile, overgiven of the openstreetmap.org api. It is used later on for drawing these tile images on the screen in the 2D Mode of GAIA. Furthermore, TileResource contains a exact position, indicated by the "tile coordinates". The tile coordinates are based upon the "Slippy-Map convention".
    Author:
    Johannes Bauer, Matthias Fisch
    See Also:
    Slippy-Map convention Each tile image comes has it's specific "style" which depends on the data source, where it comes from. But the TileResource object don't contain this information - only the TileResourceManager is responsible to differ between the different styles of tiles., TileResourceManager, Serialized Form

      • TileResource

        public TileResource(IntegerVector3D tileCoord)
             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Initializes the tile-resource with its coordinates (see SlippyMap-convention).
        Parameters:
        tileCoord - The coordinates of the tile. The z-component of the vector defines the zoom-level.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the x- or y-coordinate is not in range [1, 2^z], whereas z is the z-component of the vector. Also the latter must be in range [1, 18].

      • setTimestamp

        public void setTimestamp(long timeStamp)
        Description copied from class: DataResource
        Sets the timestamp of this resource. This may either be a logical or UNIX-timestamp used to create a happened-before-relationship between resources. In both cases the semantics must be defined in a way fulfilling the following condition: If t1 is the timestamp of r1 and t2 the timestamp of r2, then t1 < t2 implies that r1 was created before r2.
        Parameters:
        timeStamp - The timestamp of the resource.
